## ✅ PHASE 3 COMPLETE: Overflow Detection (Fits-or-Fails) (2026-01-12)

**STATUS: BUG FIXED - OVERFLOW DETECTION WORKING**

Fixed critical parser bug preventing overflow detection from working.

### Bug Fix
Parser was creating `LiteralExpr` with hardcoded `(int64_t)0` when `raw_text` was set, completely ignoring the actual token value. This made all overflow checks fail.

**Root Cause**: In `parser.cpp` line ~447:
```cpp
// BROKEN:
if (!raw_text.empty()) {
    return std::make_shared<LiteralExpr>((int64_t)0, raw_text, line, col, true);
}
```

**Fix**: Use token value for normal literals, raw_text only for true high-precision overflow:
```cpp
// FIXED:
std::string raw_text = token.raw_literal_text;
int64_t value = token.value.int_value;

if (value != 0 || raw_text.empty()) {
    // Normal literal - use parsed value
    return LiteralExpr::makeTypedInt(value, type_str, line, col);
} else {
    // High-precision - use raw_text
    return LiteralExpr::makeTypedIntWithRaw(value, raw_text, type_str, line, col);
}
```

